					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">When VBlank hits, an NMI is generated. That's what yo use to determine it. either run code in the NMI, of make the NMI do something a loop in the main code looks for:<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/NMI_thread">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/NMI_thread</a><!-- m --><br /><br />That may help. My NMI is just:<br /><br />INC Frame<br /><br />and a loop sits comparing waiting the frame value to change, because when it does you know a vblank happened and you're in vblank then. This is only good for games that don't use all the frame time, though.</div>

