					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The proper way to wait for VBlank is to put something in your NMI that will alert the program that VBlank has happened. A common solution is to put <strong>INC FrameCounter</strong> somewhere in your NMI handler, so that you can wait for VBlank by waiting for that variable to change:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp;lda FrameCounter<br />WaitForVBlank:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;cmp FrameCounter<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;beq WaitForVBlank</div><br />Just do this before turning rendering on or off and you'll never get half-rendered screens.<br /><br />The code you currently have is just an arbitrary delay that may happen to work given the current conditions, but if you change anything else that affects the timing it might stop working. Don't use that kind of hardcoded delays to wait for an event that is reported by the machine, there's no need to &quot;guess&quot; when VBlank will happen if the machine tells you when it does.</div><br /><br />One question though, how many frames should I set to the framecounter to wait?</div>

