					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">mysteriousity wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">One question though, how many frames should I set to the framecounter to wait?</div><br />You're don't really need to wait for a number of frames to wait for VBlank, just waiting for the flag to change is enough. The code I wrote will work even if you don't initialize <strong>FrameCounter</strong> at all. Notice how after loading the value the loop keeps comparing it to the variable, which will only be changed by the NMI, once it fires. As you can see, no matter the value it will be changed by the NMI handler, so you'll know that VBlank has started.<br /><br />You can use <strong>FrameCounter</strong> as an actual frame counter for other purposes if you want to... personally I don't see much use for that, but if you think that a value that's incremented once per frame can help you in other areas of your game, I see no reason for you not to use it.</div>

